<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                McMahon</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-11-27"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 27, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your interesting dispatch from Rio de
                            Janeiro, No. 6, of the 26th ultimo, has been received.</p>
                        <p>The instruction, No. 7, of the 21st instant, makes it unnecessary to
                            write to you further upon the subject at present.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Martin T. McMahon</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>